sentences: By 1908, he was playing in Storyville, the red-light district of New Orleans.
In 1918, Jones moved to Chicago, Illinois.
Jones began recording in 1923, making gramophone records as a piano soloist, accompanist to vocalists, and with his bands The Jazz Wizards and The Chicago Cosmopolitans.
He recorded for Gennett, OKeh, Victor, and Paramount Records in the 1920s.
In the 1930s, Jones performed a similar management role for Decca.
Richard M. Jones worked for Mercury Records until his death in December 1945 in Chicago, at the age of 53.

sentences: Richard M. Jones, born Richard Marigny Jones (sometimes written Richard Mariney Jones), (June 13, 1892 – December 8, 1945) was an American jazz pianist, composer, band leader, and record producer.
A few years later, he often led a small band which sometimes included Joe Oliver.
He also worked for OKeh Records as Chicago supervisor of the company's "Race" (African-American) Records for most of the decade.
